)@@G@@SUBROUTINE NEWVAR(NV)   @^@[@@00756    119.     C     @J@[@@00756    120DV
)@@G@@.     C      SUBROUTINE TO COMPUTE A NEW VARIABLE BASED ON MARITAL STATUDW
)@@G@@S     @G@[@@00756    121.     C      DATE OF LAST MARRIAGE, AND NUMBER ODX
)@@G@@F CHILDREN  @^@[@@00756    122.     C     @E@[@@00761    123.           DY
)@@G@@IF(MST.LE.0 .OR. MST.GT.6) GO TO 100@C@[@@00763    124.           IF(MSTDZ
)@@G@@.EQ.1) NV=' 1'    @E@[@@00765    125.           IF(MST.EQ.2 .AND. NCH.LEEA
)@@G@@.0) NV=' 2' @E@[@@00767    126.           IF(MST.EQ.2 .AND. NCH.GE.1) NVEB
)@@G@@=' 3' @E@[@@00771    127.           IF(MST.EQ.3 .AND. NCH.LE.0) NV=' 4' EC
)@@G@@@E@[@@00773    128.           IF(MST.EQ.3 .AND. NCH.GE.1) NV=' 5' @^@[@@ED
)@@G@@00773    129.     C     @D@[@@00773    130.     C      CHECK FOR WIDOWEDEE
)@@G@@ STATUS     @^@[@@00773    131.     C     @C@[@@00775    132.           EF
)@@G@@IF(MST.NE.4) GO TO 50   @H@[@@00775    133.     C      CHECK FOR OVER 5 EG
)@@G@@YRS. SINCE MOST RECENT DISSOLUTION  @ @[@@00777    134.           CALL OEH
)@@G@@(^@@@@VERFV(D1,D2,D3,IND)     @C@[@@01000    135.           IF(NCH.GT.0)EI
)@@G@@ GO TO 40   @C@[@@01002    136.           IF(IND.EQ.1) NV=' 6'    @C@[@@EJ
)@@G@@01004    137.           IF(IND.EQ.2) NV=' 8'    @C@[@@01006    138.     EK
)@@G@@      IF(IND.EQ.-1) NV='  '   @A@[@@01010    139.           GO TO 200   EL
)@@G@@@B@[@@01010    140.     C      HAS CHILDREN     @C@[@@01011    141.     EM
)@@G@@   40 IF(IND.EQ.1) NV=' 7'    @C@[@@01013    142.           IF(IND.EQ.2)EN
)@@G@@ NV=' 9'    @C@[@@01015    143.           IF(IND.EQ.-1) NV='  '   @A@[@@EO
)@@G@@01017    144.           GO TO 200   @^@[@@01017    145.     C     @E@[@@EP
)@@G@@01017    146.     C      CHECK FOR DIVORCED OR SEPARATED    @^@[@@01017 EQ
)@@G@@   147.     C     @F@[@@01020    148.        50 IF(MST.NE.5 .AND. MST.NEER
)@@G@@.6) GO TO 200     @D@[@@01022    149.           CALL OVERFV(D1,D2,D3,INDES
)@@G@@)     @C@[@@01023    150.           IF(NCH.GT.0) GO TO 60   @C@[@@01025 ET
)@@G@@   151.           IF(IND.EQ.1) NV='10'    @C@[@@01027    152.           EU
)@@G@@IF(IND.EQ.2) NV='12'    @C@[@@01031    153.           IF(IND.EQ.-1) NV='EV
)@@G@@  '   @A@[@@01033    154.           GO TO 200   @F@[@@01033    155.     EW
)@@G@@C      HAS CHILDREN (DIVORCED OR SEPARATED)     @C@[@@01034    156.     EX
)@@G@@   60 IF(IND.EQ.1) NV='11'    @C@[@@01036    157.           IF(IND.EQ.2)EY
)@@G@@ NV='13'    @C@[@@01040    158.           IF(IND.EQ.-1) NV='  '   @A@[@@EZ
)@@G@@01042    159.           GO TO 200   @[@[@@01042 (E@@@@   160.     C     FA
)@@G@@ NO MARITAL STATUS INFO ON INPUT RECORD   @A@[@@01043    161.       100 FB
)@@G@@NV='  '     @ @[@@01044    162.       200 RETURN@^@[@@01044    163.     FC
)@@G@@C     @J@[@@01044    164.     C*****************************************FD
)@@G@@******************************@^@[@@01044    165.     C     @E@[@@01045 FE

)@@G@@RAMS HE TURNED OUT, AND FOR DARING TO     @B@@@@ USE RALPH IN CLASS PROJIA

)@@G@@RE DUMPS.   @[@@@@      @F@@@@       FINALLY, THANKS GO TO MR. ALFRED BEIC
)@@G@@AM FOR HIS GUIDANCE,    @F@@@@ INSPIRATION, AND PRODDING; THE ENTIRE RALID
)@@G@@PH PROJECT WAS CONCEIVED@ @@@@ AND ORGANIZED BY MR. BEAM.   @[@@@@      IE

)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@CAL IS CAPABLE OF QUICKLY DETERMINING THE DAY OF WEEK MK
)@@G@@FOR ANY     @E@@@@DATE WITHIN ITS RANGE (1753-9999), AND OF PRINTING FULML
)@@G@@L-PAGE@F@@@@DISPLAYS (WITH PICTURES, EVEN!) FOR ANY MONTH, OR FOR EACH MMM
)@@G@@ONTH  @#@@@@OF A GIVEN YEAR.  @[@@@@      @ @@@@THE CALL IS SIMPLY:   @CMN
)@@G@@AL    @E@@@@                      (DATA CARD(S) AS DESCRIBED BELOW)     MO
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@TO FIND THE DAY OF WEEK FOR A SPECIFIC DATE, ENTER THEMP
)@@G@@ MONTH,     @ @@@@DAY, AND YEAR IN COLUMNS 1-10.@[@@@@      @ @@@@  EXAMMQ
)@@G@@PLE:     06/16/1950     @[@@@@      @F@@@@TO PRINT THE CALENDAR FOR A SPMR
)@@G@@ECIFIC MONTH, ENTER ONLY THE MONTH  @C@@@@AND THE YEAR, LEAVING THE DAY MS
)@@G@@BLANK OR ZERO.    @[@@@@      @ @@@@  EXAMPLE:     10/00/1852     @[@@@@MT
)@@G@@      @E@@@@FOR A COMPLETE YEAR'S CALENDARS, LEAVE THE MONTH, AS WELL ASMU
)@@G@@@#@@@@THE DAY, BLANK.   @[@@@@      @ @@@@  EXAMPLE:     00/00/1984     MV
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @E@@@@HOLIDAYS MAY BE ADDED TO MONTHLY AND YEARLY CALENDARS MW
)@@G@@BY    @F@@@@SPECIFYING THE MONTH AND DAY OF THE DESIRED HOLIDAY, LEAVINGMX
)@@G@@ THE  @F@@@@YEAR BLANK.  THE NAME OF THE HOLIDAY, WHICH MAY NOT EXCEED 7MY
)@@G@@ WORDS@E@@@@AND/OR 12 CHARACTERS PER WORD, FOLLOWS IN COLUMNS 11-80.    MZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @B@@@@  EXAMPLES:    01/01     NEW YEAR'S DAY   @B@@@@      NA
)@@G@@         11/27     THANKSGIVING DAY @[@@@@      @E@@@@UP TO 100 HOLIDAYSNB
)@@G@@ MAY BE USED IN ONE RUN.  THEY SHOULD BE  @F@@@@INSERTED -BEFORE- THE MONC
)@@G@@NTH OR YEAR TO BE PRINTED, AND WILL BE    @G@@@@HONORED FOR ALL SUBSEQUEND
)@@G@@NT CALENDARS GENERATED BY THIS CALL ON @CAL.    @E@@@@THE CHARACTER '@' NE
)@@G@@WITHIN A HOLIDAY NAME WILL BE COUNTED AS A@F@@@@REGULAR CHARACTER, BUT INF
)@@G@@S PRINTED AS A SPACE, THUS ALLOWING MORE  @F@@@@THAN ONE WORD PER LINE FNG
)@@G@@PR THE HOLIDAY (NORMALLY, @CAL PUTS ONE   @G@@@@WORD ON EACH HOLIDAY LINNH
)@@G@@E, AND CENTERS THEM).  IF A HOLIDAY NAME IS     @F@@@@TOO LONG TO FIT ONNI
)@@G@@ ONE CARD, PUT A '+' IN COLUMN 80 OF THAT CARD, @F@@@@AND CONTINUE THE HNJ
)@@G@@OLIDAY NAME ON THE NEXT CARD, STARTING IN COLUMN@F@@@@2.  NOTE THAT IMBENK
)@@G@@DDED BLANKS SIGNIFY THE ENDS OF WORDS, AND THAT @E@@@@TWO OR MORE BLANKSNL
)@@G@@ IN A ROW SIGNIFY THE END OF THE IMAGE.   @[@@@@*****^@G@@@@WHEN PRODUCINM
)@@G@@NG A MONTHLY OR YEARLY CALENDAR, ONE MAY ELECT TO USE THE   @F@@@@BUILT-NN
)@@G@@IN RANDOM SYMMETRICAL DESIGN ROUTINE, OR COMBINE THAT WITH  @G@@@@RANDOMNO
)@@G@@ TITLES FOR THE DESIGNS.  THIS IS ACCOMPLISHED VIA ONE-LETTER     @F@@@@NP
)@@G@@OPTIONS FOLLOWING THE YEAR ON THE DATA CARD.  THE OPTION LETTER   @F@@@@NQ
)@@G@@GOES IN COLUMN 11.  THE LETTER 'N' IS USED IF NO DESIGNS OR TITLES@F@@@@NR
)@@G@@ARE DESIRED, WHILE A BLANK IN COLUMN 11 MEANS THAT A DESIGN IS    @F@@@@NS
)@@G@@WANTED, BUT NO TITLES ARE TO BE PRINTED.  THE LETTER 'T' ENABLES  @A@@@@NT
)@@G@@BOTH THE DESIGN AND TITLE ROUTINES. @[@@@@      @ @@@@  EXAMPLE:     00/NU
)@@G@@00/1972T    @[@@@@      @E@@@@THIS WOULD PRODUCE MONTHLY CALENDARS FOR TNV
)@@G@@HE YEAR 1972,     @B@@@@COMPLETE WITH RANDOM PICTURES AND TITLES. @[@@@@NW
)@@G@@      @G@@@@  NOTE - THE SLASHES SHOWN IN THE EXAMPLES ABOVE ARE OPTIONANX
)@@G@@L.  ANY     @E@@@@         CHARACTER, INCLUDING THE BLANK, MAY BE SUBSTINY
)@@G@@TUTED.@[@@@@      @F@@@@AS AN ADDITIONAL FEATURE, PERSONALIZED MESSAGES NZ
)@@G@@MAY BE DISPLAYED  @F@@@@ON MONTHLY OR YEARLY CALENDARS BY ADDING ANOTHEROA
)@@G@@ FIELD TO THE DATA@G@@@@CARD.  TYPE 'DUFF' IN COLUMNS 12-15, AND THEN THOB
)@@G@@E NUMBER OF LINES IN    @F@@@@YOUR MESSAGE (UP TO 5) IN COLUMN 16.  EACHOC
)@@G@@ LINE OF THE MESSAGE MAY@F@@@@BE UP TO 30 CHARACTERS LONG, TYPED ON SEPAOD
)@@G@@RATE CARDS IMMEDIATELY  @E@@@@FOLLOWING THE CALENDAR DATA CARD.  CENTERIOE
)@@G@@NG OF THE MESSAGE @A@@@@WITHIN THE 30 SPACES IS SUGGESTED.  @[@@@@      OF
)@@G@@@^@@@@  EXAMPLE:     1  @CAL  @A@@@@               2  01/00/1975NDUFF2  OG
)@@G@@@B@@@@               3       COMPLIMENTS OF     @B@@@@               4  OH
)@@G@@  UHMC COMPUTER CENTER  @[@@@@      @F@@@@FROM DEMAND TERMINALS, HOLIDAYOI
)@@G@@S, MESSAGE, PICTURES, AND TITLES    @F@@@@WILL BE IGNORED, AND A SMALLEROJ
)@@G@@ CALENDAR WILL BE PRINTED.  THIS    @F@@@@AUTOMATIC FEATURE MAY BE OVERROK
)@@G@@IDDEN BY TWO MORE OPTION LETTERS    @F@@@@PUT IN COLUMN 11 OF ANY DATA COL
)@@G@@ARD EXCEPT THOSE FOR HOLIDAYS AND   @F@@@@MESSAGES.  THE LETTER 'D' SWITOM
)@@G@@CHES THE PROGRAM TO 'DEMAND' MODE,  @E@@@@WHILE 'B' SWITCHES IT TO 'BATCON
)@@G@@H' MODE.  WHEN USING THE @CAL @G@@@@PROCESSOR FROM A TELETYPE, THE 'B' OOO
)@@G@@PTION SHOULD ONLY BE USED IF YOU    @F@@@@ARE BREAKPOINTING THE PRINTOUTOP
)@@G@@ TO A FILE FOR SUBSEQUENT SYMMING   @#@@@@TO A PRINTER.     @[@@@@      OQ
)@@G@@___ULAR CHARACTER, BUT IS PRINTED AS A SPACE, THUS ALLOWING MORE  @F@@@@OR
)@@G@@THAN ONE WORD PER LINE FPR THE HOLIDAY (NORMALLY*[@@@@*SDFF*@E@@@@ @CONDOS
)@@G@@ SIMPLY PRINTS THE CURRENT VALUE OF THE CONDITION WORD@C@@@@ IN OCTAL.  OT
)@@G@@THE PROCESSOR CALL IS JUST @COND.   ___ETJEK)CT[D-G^[DES)DLPETO^[@CTJD1^OU
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@E@@@@LOOKEQ IS A FORTRAN SUBROUTINE ENABLING FORTRAN PROGRAOV
)@@G@@MS TO @G@@@@SEARCH TABLES USING THE HIGH SPPED SEARCH FUNCTION OF THE UNOW
)@@G@@IVAC 1108.  @D@@@@FOR DETAILS, SEE THE LONG VERSION OF THIS LISTING.    OX
)@@G@@@[@@@@******@[@@@@      @^@@@@THE LOOKEQ CALL IS:     @[@@@@      @A@@@@OY
)@@G@@         I=LOOKEQ(ARG,TAB,LEN,MASK) @[@@@@      @F@@@@     ARG IS THE ITOZ
)@@G@@EM BEING SEARCHED FOR, E.G. IF YOU ARE SEARCHING@F@@@@ FOR THE FIRST OCCPA
)@@G@@URENCE OF THE NUMBER 3.25279841, THEN YOU WOULD @ @@@@ SET ARG EQUAL TO PB
)@@G@@3.25279841. @B@@@@     TAB IS THE TABLE TO BE SEARCHED.     @A@@@@     LPC
)@@G@@EN IS THE LENGTH OF THE TABLE.@F@@@@     I WILL BE SET EQUAL TO THE INDEPD
)@@G@@X INTO THE TABLE WHERE THE    @F@@@@ CONTENTS OF ARG WERE FOUND. IF THERPE
)@@G@@E WAS NO FIND, I WILL BE SET  @]@@@@ TO ZERO.   @F@@@@     MASK, IF SET PF
)@@G@@NONZERO, WILL CAUSE THE SEARCH TO BE A MASKED   @F@@@@ SEARCH. THAT IS, PG
)@@G@@IF THE MASK HAS THE VALUE 077770000 OCTAL, THE  @E@@@@ SEARCH WILL CONSIPH
)@@G@@DER ONLY THE MIDDLE THIRD OF EACH WORD.   @[@@@@      @]@@@@ EXAMPLE:   PI
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @ @@@@         DIMENSION LIST(35)   @ @@@@         LIST(12)=PJ
)@@G@@'KEPOOT'    @C@@@@         I=LOOKEQ('CAHOOT',LIST,35,0777777)     @[@@@@PK
)@@G@@      @F@@@@     THIS WILL SEARCH THE 35 WORDS OF THE ARRAY LIST, LOOKINPL
)@@G@@G FOR @F@@@@ THR FIRST WORD WHOSE BOTTOM HALF IS THE SAME AS THE BOTTOM PM
)@@G@@HALF  @F@@@@ OF 'CAHOOT'. IT WILL RETURN A VALUE 12, BECAUSE THE BOTTOM PN
)@@G@@HALF  @F@@@@ OF LIST(12)='OOT', THE SAME AS THE BOTTOM HALF OF THE ARGUMPO
)@@G@@ENT.  @[@@@@      @]@@@@ NOTES:     @[@@@@      @E@@@@     THE RESULT WIPP
)@@G@@LL BE MOST USEFUL IF THE TABLE IS A ONE-  @F@@@@ DIMENSIONED ARRAY, BECAPQ
)@@G@@USE IN THAT CASE THE VALUE OF I MAY BE    @^@@@@ USED AS A SUBSCRIPT.   PR
)@@G@@@D@@@@     IF MASKING IS NOT DESIRED, SPECIFY O AS THE MASK.@F@@@@     UPS
)@@G@@SERS OF THE @MAD COMPILER WILL NOT NEED THIS ROUTINE, BUT   @F@@@@ MAY IPT
)@@G@@NSTEAD USE THE .FIND. AND .SEARCH. FUNCTIONS OF THE MAD     @]@@@@ COMPIPU
)@@G@@LER.  ___ET ^[OD[ ^[]D9OE-JD*)D[[D-A@K@@@@^[JC0)D-DETO @1AK(B*$D9JE)$ ))PV
)@@G@@E-CC*)ET[D( ^[[ES)E-CC*)CLJE-OD9H^[CCDGC0)D9A^[OD[ ^[[ELBE(HC(IE),@[@@@@PW
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@TDUMP IS A UTILITY TAPE-DUMPING ROUTINE.  DETAILS THE PX
)@@G@@THE LONG VERSION  @#@@@@OF THIS ITEM.     @[@@@@******@[@@@@      @ @@@@PY
)@@G@@         TAPE DUMP ROUTINE    @A@@@@         WILL DUMP ANY 7-TRACK TAPE PZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@         RECORDS MUST BE < 2000WORDS (SEE 'G' OPTION) @[@@@@      QA
)@@G@@@B@@@@         @TDUMP,OPTIONS      FILENAME.,N  @[@@@@      @B@@@@      QB
)@@G@@   N IS # OF FILES TO DUMP (<9)     @[@@@@      @#@@@@ OPTIONS ARE:     QC
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @^@@@@          O FOR OCTAL   @ @@@@          F FOR FLOATINGQD
)@@G@@ POINT@B@@@@          A FOR ALPHANUMERIC (FIELDATA)   @^@@@@          I QE
)@@G@@FOR INTEGER @B@@@@          B PICK UP USER-SUPPLIED FORMAT  @D@@@@      QF
)@@G@@    G FOR 2K MORE BUFFER  (TOTAL=4K RECORDS)    @C@@@@          C FOR SEQG
)@@G@@LECTIVE DUMPING (SEE BELOW)   @B@@@@          T FOR TRANSLATE (BCD-FIELDQH
)@@G@@ATA)  @C@@@@          N TO SUPPRESS PRINTING OF RECORD COUNT@D@@@@      QI
)@@G@@    R TO REWIND TAPE WHEN DONE (@REWIND WON'T)  @C@@@@          S TO RECQJ
)@@G@@OGNIZE SOFTWARE (SDF) EOF     @D@@@@              (IE,77K IN S1 OF FIRSTQK
)@@G@@ WORD OF RECORD)  @C@@@@          X FOR PARTIAL DUMP - (10 RECORDS)     QL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          Z TO PRINT EVEN THOUGH UNRECOVERABLE PARITY ERRORS@[@@@@QM
)@@G@@      @B@@@@     FILENAME MUST END WITH A PERIOD (.)  @E@@@@     TAPE SHQN
)@@G@@OULD BE @ASG'D WITH PROPER DENSITY IF KNOWN.    @B@@@@     SELECTIVE DUMQO
)@@G@@PING WITH 'C' OPTION:   @#@@@@     COMMANDS     @ @@@@     COMMAND FORM QP
)@@G@@- COMMAND/N @ @@@@     ALLOWABLE COMMANDS ARE   @[@@@@      @D@@@@      QQ
)@@G@@ DUMPA - DUMP N RECORDS IN ALPHANUMERIC FORMAT  @C@@@@       DUMPO - DUMQR
)@@G@@P N RECORDS IN OCTAL FORMAT   @ @@@@       SKIPF - SKIP N FILES   @C@@@@QS
)@@G@@       SKIPR - SKIP N RECORDS (STOPS AT EOR)    @A@@@@       BSF   - BACQT
)@@G@@KSPACE N RECORDS  @A@@@@       BSR   - BACKSPACE N RECORDS  @B@@@@      QU
)@@G@@         (EOR COUNTS AS A RECORD)   @[@@@@      @D@@@@     PROCESSOR CALQV
)@@G@@L CARD FORMAT FOR SELECTIVE DUMPING:@[@@@@      @E@@@@     @TDUMP,C   FIQW
)@@G@@LENAME.,DUMPA/100,BSR/15,DUMPO/30,SKIPF/2 @[@@@@      @ @@@@     DUMPA &QX
)@@G@@ DUMPO STOP AT EOF@C@@@@     T.N.S & Z OPTIONS ALLOWED WITH C OPTION    QY
)@@G@@@E@@@@     UP TO 30 COMMANDS ALLOWED, FOLLOW EXEC CONVENTIONS     @B@@@@QZ
)@@G@@     FOR CONTINUATION OF CONTROL CARDS    @[@@@@      @F@@@@ NOTE:  NO FRA

)@@G@@  5.10.   SIDE EFFECTS  @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @G@@@@      SIDE EFFECTSNL

)@@G@@ DEGREE  OR OTHER.   ALTHOUGH THE ORIGINAL DESIGNERS OF APL[3] WERE     NP

)@@G@@ADDCN1    LXM,U     X4,ADDTBL @^@@@@          LXI,U     X4,1@ @@@@      ZJ
)@@G@@    L         A2,ADDL   @ @@@@          S         A2,R1     @ @@@@      ZK
)@@G@@    L         R2,MASK2  @ @@@@          MSE       A0,0,*X4  @ @@@@      ZL

)@@G@@    L         R2,SAVE+1 @A@@@@          AND       A0,(0777777)    @ @@@@ZN
)@@G@@          L,U       A3,0,X4   @^@@@@          AN,U      A3,1@ @@@@      ZO
)@@G@@    AN,H2     A1,0,A3   @ @@@@          S         A1,A0     @ @@@@ADDCN2ZP

)@@G@@8     @ @@@@          S         A0,4,A3   @ @@@@          L,U       A0,0ZX

)@@G@@        ADDCN2    @ @@@@ADDCN1    LXM,U     X4,A*[@@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@$(1)  AU
)@@G@@    AXR$    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DYNAMIC SEGMENT MCORE ROUTINE - CHUNK OFAV
)@@G@@ 'DLOAD$' RLIB$ ELEMENT @[@@@@.     @G@@@@DSEG*     LSSL      A1,2      AW
)@@G@@          . CONVERT SEGID TO SLT INDEX    @F@@@@          A,U       A1,SAX
)@@G@@LT$             . GET ADDR OF SLT ENTRY   @G@@@@          L,S2      A0,,AY
)@@G@@A1              . TEST IF SEG DEFINED AS DSEG   @B@@@@          TE,U    AZ
)@@G@@  A0,011              . @B@@@@          TNE,U     A0,010              . BA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         $+2                 . IS A DSEG - CONTINUE    BB
)@@G@@@#@@[@          NOP     @F[@@@          L,H1      A0,1,A1             . BC
)@@G@@LOAD IBANK ADDR NEEDED  @H@@@@          L,S2      A2,SLT$             . BD
)@@G@@DETERMINE IF SLT FORMAT COMPLEX     @B@@@@          TNE,U     A2,022    BE
)@@G@@          . @E@@@@          J         DLOAD0              . IF COMPLEX, BF
)@@G@@DLOAD0@F@@@@          JZ        A0,$+3              . CHECK FOR VOID SEGBG
)@@G@@MENT  @G@@@@          A         A0,(1*/34)          . SET PROGRAM-WIDE BBH
)@@G@@IT FOR MCORE@D@@@@          ER        MCORE$              . EXPAND IBANKBI
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L,H1      A0,2,A1             . LOAD DBANK ADDR NEEDED  BJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JZ        A0,DLOAD2           . CHECK FOR VOID SEG@E@@@@BK
)@@G@@          A         A0,(1*/34)          . SET PGM-WIDE BIT  @D@@@@      BL
)@@G@@    ER        MCORE$              . EXPAND DBANK@D@@@@          J       BM
)@@G@@  DLOAD2              . CONTINUE    @G@@@@DLOAD0    L         A2,A1     BN
)@@G@@          . SAVE INITIAL SLT ENTRY ADDR   @E@@@@DLOAD1    JZ        A0,$BO
)@@G@@+4              . CHECK FOR VOID SEG@F@@@@          LXI,T1    A0,2,A2   BP
)@@G@@          . LOAD BDI FOR THIS BANK  @E@@@@          A         A0,(1*/34)BQ
)@@G@@          . SET PGM-WIDE BIT  @D@@@@          ER        MCORE$          BR
)@@G@@    . EXPAND BANK @G@@@@          L,H2      A2,2,A2             . LOAD LBS
)@@G@@INK TO NEXT EXTENSION   @G@@@@          JZ        A2,DLOAD2           . BT
)@@G@@JUMP IF ALL EXTENSIONS DONE   @F@@@@          A,U       A2,SLT$         BU
)@@G@@    . COMPUTE EXTENSION ADDR  @F@@@@          L,H2      A0,1,A2         BV
)@@G@@    . LOAD BANK ADDR NEEDED   @F@@@@          J         DLOAD1          BW
)@@G@@    . CONTINUE EXPANSION LOOP @F@@@@DLOAD2    L,U       A2,024          BX
)@@G@@    . MARK SEG AS OVERLAY SEG @B@@@@          S,S2      A2,,A1          BY
)@@G@@    . @C@@@@          J         0,X11               . RETURN@#@@@@      BZ
)@@G@@    END     ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@CA
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@SEG  MAIN   @ @@@@IN   MFD,DSECB

)@@G@@GURATION PARAMETERS     @D@@@@          EQUFS                         . DF
)@@G@@DEFINE TAGS @E@@@@ERRMSG    'MFD ERROR TYPE & CODE &'     . DIREC$ ERRORDG
)@@G@@ MSG  @^@@@@. DIREC$ ERROR ROUTINE  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@DIRECERR* LXI     DH
)@@G@@  X11,X11             . SAVE RETURN ADDR IN UPPER X11 @E@@@@          LADI
)@@G@@        A0,ECODE            . GET ERROR TYPE    @D@@@@          TE,U    DJ
)@@G@@  A0,3                . DIRSEC EOF? @C@@_@          J         ERR100    DK
)@@G@@          . NO    @ @@@@          ON        SORTOK    @E@@@@          TZDL
)@@G@@        SORT                . SORT DESIRED?     @D@@@@          J       DM
)@@G@@  DOSORT              . YES, DO IT  @ @@@@          OFF       SORTOK    DN
)@@G@@@E@@_@          J         MFD600              . NO, FINISH UP     @D@@_@DO
)@@G@@ERR100    E$DIT     EDPACK              . OPEN EDIT   @E@@@@          E$DP
)@@G@@MSG     ERRMSG              . EDIT START OF MSG @E@@@@          E$DECV  DQ
)@@G@@  ECODE               . EDIT ERROR TYPE   @F@@@@          TNZ       ECODDR
)@@G@@E+1             . ERROR CODE PRESENT?     @E@@_@          J         ERR2DS
)@@G@@00              . NO, PRINT MSG     @D@@@@          E$MSGR              DT
)@@G@@          . CONTINUE MSG@E@@@@          E$OCTF    12,ECODE+1          . DU
)@@G@@EDIT ERROR CODE   @D@@_@ERR200    P$RINT    POUT                . PRINT DV
)@@G@@MSG   @D@@@@          L         A0,X11              . GET X11     @G@@@@DW
)@@G@@          SSL       A0,18               . ISOLATE DIRECERR RTN SAVE     DX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LXI,U     X11,0               . PREVENT LOOPS     @B@@@@DY
)@@G@@          AN,U      A0,LNKRTN           . @G@@@@          SR        R15,DZ
)@@G@@BMI1            . MARK AS BAD MAIN ITEM SEC 1   @G@@@@          JZ      EA
)@@G@@  A0,CHK220           . TO 'MIJP' IF FROM 'GOLINK'    @D@@_@          J EB
)@@G@@        MFD700              . ELSE EXIT   @#@@@@          END     ___E[MEC
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@LEVEL*    . @#@@@@          '6.4'   @#@@@@          ENED

)@@G@@___@_@C[HCDK -]D0)^[HCDK -HC1^ 9AD-[E@)^@)@[@@_@*[@@@@*SDFF*@^@@_@. @MFDEH
)@@G@@ PRINT2 ROUTINE   @[@@_@      @G@@_@. CALLED BY PRINT ROUTINE IF ADDITIOEI
)@@G@@NAL LINES ARE NEEDED FOR MULTIPLE   @E@@_@. TAPE REELS, DISC PACKS, AND/EJ
)@@G@@OR SECURE BACKUPS.  ALSO EDITS@G@@_@. LAPSE ENTRIES AND EXTRA INFORMATIOEK
)@@G@@N PROVIDED BY FITEM$ WHEN THE 'QF'  @^@@_@. OPTIONS ARE USED.     @[@@@@EL
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@          AXR$    @H@@@@          CONFIG                    EM
)@@G@@    . DEFINE CONFIGURATION PARAMETERS     @D@@@@          EQUFS         EN
)@@G@@                . DEFINE TAGS @E@@@@MI2       RES       28              EO
)@@G@@    . MI 2-N BUFFER     @^@@@@LINK      RES       1   @#@@@@MORE      'MEP
)@@G@@ORE &'@^@@_@PACKS     'PACKS:&'     @^@@@@REELS     'REELS:&'     @^@@@@EQ
)@@G@@BAKS      'BACKUPS:&'   @B@@@@LAPS      'LAPSE FROM & AT & TO & AT &'   ER
)@@G@@@E@@@@TAP1      'UNIT: &  REELS: &  INDEX: &  CURRENT: &  NEXT: &'@B@@@@ES
)@@G@@TAP2      'NOISE: &FILES EXTENDED: &'     @ @@@@TAP3      'BLOCKS EXTENDET
)@@G@@ED: &'@^@@@@COL1      EQU       5   @^@@@@COL2      EQU       19  @^@@@@EU
)@@G@@COL3      EQU       124 @^@@@@COL4      EQU       64  @^@@@@PAKBIT    EQEV
)@@G@@U       040 @^@@@@BAKBIT    EQU       020 @^@@@@LPSBIT    EQU       010 EW
)@@G@@@#@@_@/$(1),PMORE*  .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. HANDLE EXTRA TAPE REELS FIRSEX
)@@G@@T     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          LA        A8,NTP              . GET NUEY
)@@G@@MBER OF EXTRA REELS     @F@@@@          JZ        A8,PM200            . EZ
)@@G@@IF NONE, SKIP TO PACKS  @D@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK              . FA
)@@G@@OPEN EDIT   @D@@@@          E$COL     COL1                . POSITION    FB
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$MSG     MORE                . 'MORE'@D@@@@          E$FC
)@@G@@MSG     REELS               . 'REELS:'    @D@@@@          E$COL     COL2FD
)@@G@@                . POSITION    @E@@@@          E$FD1     MI0+27          FE
)@@G@@    . EDIT SECOND REEL  @E@@@@          AN,U      A8,1                . FF
)@@G@@ONE LESS TO DO    @F@@@@          JZ        A8,PM110            . PRINT FG
)@@G@@IF THAT'S ALL     @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,MI0              . FIRST FH
)@@G@@LINK WORD ADDR    @B@@@@          J         $+2                 . @F@@@@FI
)@@G@@PM100     LA,U      A0,MI2              . GET NEXT LINK WORD ADDR @E@@@@FJ
)@@G@@          LMJ       X10,GETNXT          . GET NEXT SECTOR   @E@@@@      FK
)@@G@@    J         PM110               . NO MORE, SO PRINT @G@@@@          LXFL
)@@G@@        X4,(1,2)            . GET SECTOR INDEX AND INCREMENT@F@@@@      FM
)@@G@@    LXI,U     X10,26              . WORD LIMIT IN SECTOR    @E@@@@      FN
)@@G@@    LMJ       X10,EDSUB           . FORM PRINT LINES  @F@@@@          J FO
)@@G@@        PM100               . NEED ANOTHER SECTOR     @E@@@@PM110     P$FP
)@@G@@RINT    POUT                . PRINT THE LINE    @ @@@@. NOW DO REMOVABLEFQ
)@@G@@ DISC PACKS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@PM200     LA        A8,NRP              . FR
)@@G@@GET NUMBER OF EXTRA PACKS     @G@@@@          JZ        A8,PM300        FS
)@@G@@    . IF NONE, GO ON TO BACKUPS     @D@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK    FT
)@@G@@          . OPEN EDIT   @D@@@@          E$COL     COL1                . FU
)@@G@@POSITION    @C@@@@          E$MSG     MORE                . 'MORE'@D@@@@FV
)@@G@@          E$MSG     PACKS               . 'PACKS:'    @D@@@@          E$FW
)@@G@@COL     COL2                . POSITION    @E@@@@          TNZ       TEMPFX
)@@G@@                . TEMPORARY FILE?   @F@@@@          J         PM208     FY
)@@G@@          . NO, HANDLE NORMALLY     @G@@@@          E$FD1     MI1+19    FZ
)@@G@@          . YES, QF SETS UP 1-WRD ENTRIES @H@@@@          LX        X4,(GA
)@@G@@1,20)           . SET INDEX AND INC FOR PACKS 3-10    @D@@@@          J GB
)@@G@@        PM210               . CONTINUE    @E@@_@PM208     E$FD1     MI1+GC
)@@G@@20              . EDIT SECOND PACKID@H@@@@          LX        X4,(2,22) GD
)@@G@@          . SET INDEX AND INC FOR PACKS 3-5     @E@@@@PM210     AN,U    GE
)@@G@@  A8,1                . ONE LESS PACK     @G@@@@          JZ        A8,PGF
)@@G@@M230            . IF NO MORE, JUST PRINT LINE   @F@@@@          E$CHAR  GG
)@@G@@  ','                 . OTHERWISE, EDIT COMMA   @D@@@@          E$SKIP  GH
)@@G@@  1                   . POSITION    @E@@@@          E$FD1     MI1,X4    GI
)@@G@@          . EDIT NEXT PACKID  @F@@@@          L,U       A0,26           GJ
)@@G@@    . ASSUME 5 2-WORD ENTRIES @E@@@@          TZ        TEMP            GK
)@@G@@    . TEMPORARY FILE?   @F@@@@          L,U       A0,27               . GL
)@@G@@YES, 10 1-WORD ENTRIES  @F@@@@          TLEM      X4,A0               . GM
)@@G@@ANY MORE IN THIS SECTOR?@E@@@@          J         PM210               . GN
)@@G@@YES, GO GET THEM  @H@@@@          AN,U      A8,1                . NO MORGO
)@@G@@E THIS SECOTR...ONE LESS TO DO@F@@@@          JZ        A8,PM230        GP
)@@G@@    . IF NO MORE, PRINT LINE  @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,MI1          GQ
)@@G@@    . FIRST LINK WORD ADDR    @B@@@@          J         $+2             GR
)@@G@@    . @F@@@@PM220     LA,U      A0,MI2              . NEXT LINK WORD ADDGS
)@@G@@R     @E@@@@          LMJ       X10,GETNXT          . GET NEXT SECTOR   GT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         PM230               . NO MORE, PRINT LINE     GU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,S1     A0,MI2+7            . GET DESCRIPTOR BITS     GV
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TOP,U     A0,PAKBIT           . IS THIS A PACKID SECTOR?GW
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         PM220               . NO, TRY NEXT SECTOR     GX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LX        X4,(2,8)            . GET SECTOR INDEX AND INCGY
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LXI,U     X10,26              . SECTOR WORD LIMIT @E@@@@GZ
)@@G@@          LMJ       X10,EDSUB           . FORM PRINT LINES  @E@@@@      HA
)@@G@@    J         PM220               . NEED NEXT SECTOR  @D@@@@PM230     P$HB
)@@G@@RINT    POUT                . PRINT LINE  @ @@@@. NOW FOR EXTRA BACKUP RHC
)@@G@@EELS  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@PM300     LA        A8,NSB              . GET NUHD
)@@G@@MBER OF EXTRA BACKUPS   @E@@@@          JZ        A8,PM400            . HE
)@@G@@IF NONE, GO ON    @D@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK              . OPEN EHF
)@@G@@DIT   @D@@@@          E$COL     COL1                . POSITION    @C@@@@HG
)@@G@@          E$MSG     MORE                . 'MORE'@D@@@@          E$MSG   HH
)@@G@@  BAKS                . 'BACKUPS:'  @D@@@@          E$COL     COL2      HI
)@@G@@          . POSITION    @F@@@@          E$FD1     MI1+12              . HJ
)@@G@@EDIT SECOND BACKUP REEL @E@@@@          AN,U      A8,1                . HK
)@@G@@ONE LESS TO DO    @F@@@@          JZ        A8,PM320            . IF NO HL
)@@G@@MORE, PRINT LINE  @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,MI1              . FIRST HM
)@@G@@LINK WORD ADDR    @B@@@@          J         $+2                 . @E@@@@HN
)@@G@@PM310     LA,U      A0,MI2              . NEXT LINK ADDR    @E@@@@      HO
)@@G@@    LMJ       X10,GETNXT          . GET NEXT SECTOR   @G@@@@          J HP
)@@G@@        PM320               . NO MORE SECTORS, SO PRINT     @F@@@@      HQ
)@@G@@    LA,S1     A0,MI2+7            . GET DESCRIPTOR BITS     @F@@@@      HR
)@@G@@    TOP,U     A0,BAKBIT           . IS THIS A BACKUP SECTOR?@F@@@@      HS
)@@G@@    J         PM310               . NO, GET NEXT SECTOR     @F@@@@      HT
)@@G@@    LX        X4,(1,8)            . GET SECTOR INDEX AND INC@E@@@@      HU
)@@G@@    LXI,U     X10,27              . SECTOR WORD LIMIT @E@@@@          LMHV
)@@G@@J       X10,EDSUB           . FORM PRINT LINES  @E@@@@          J       HW
)@@G@@  PM310               . NEED NEXT SECTOR  @^@@@@PM320     P$RINT    POUTHX
)@@G@@@#@@@@. LAPSE EDITING   @[@@@@.     @G@@_@PM400     LA        A8,NLPS   HY
)@@G@@          . GET NUMBER OF LAPSE ENTRIES   @F@@@@          JZ        A8,PHZ
)@@G@@M500            . IF NONE, WE'RE THROUGH  @F@@@@          LX        X4,(IA
)@@G@@2,MI1+13)       . GET MI1 INC AND INDEX   @E@@@@PM410     LMJ       X10,IB
)@@G@@LPSED           . EDIT LAPSE ENTRY  @D@@@@          TLEM,U    X4,MI1+15 IC
)@@G@@          . THAT ALL?   @E@@@@          J         PM410               . ID
)@@G@@NO, GET NEXT ONE  @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,MI1              . GET FIIE
)@@G@@RST LINK ADDR     @B@@@@          J         $+2                 . @E@@@@IF

)@@G@@/.  SPEC4-N SPECIAL TEST SUBROUTINE @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PERFORM ALL SPECZC
)@@G@@4-N TESTS, PUTTING RESULTS IN POLISH TABLE@D@@@@. IF TEST PASSES, RESULTZD
)@@G@@ = 1.  IF FAILURE, RESULT = 0.@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. LINKAGE IS:   LMJ   X1ZE
)@@G@@1,CHK900   OR   LMJ   X11,CHK905    @B@@@@.               <DEFINITE FAILZF
)@@G@@URE RETURN> @B@@@@.               <DEFINITE SUCCESS RETURN> @E@@@@.     ZG
)@@G@@          <RETURN TO TRANSLATE POLISH EXPRESSION>     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ZH
)@@G@@. CHK900 IS ENTRY POINT FOR LEAD ITEM CHECKS.  ALL LEAD ITEM TESTS@G@@@@ZI
)@@G@@. ARE DONE, BUT RESULT OF ALL MAIN ITEM TESTS IS ASSUMED TO BE 1 (PASS).ZJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CHK905 IS ENTRY POINT FOR MAIN ITEM CHECKS.  ALL TESZK
)@@G@@TS ARE DONE IN    @]@@@@. THIS CASE.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. 'DEFINITE FAILURZL
)@@G@@E' AND 'DEFINITE SUCCESS' RETURNS ARE TAKEN ONLY IF   @F@@@@. NO OR'S ORZM
)@@G@@ XOR'S WERE DONE (JUST AND'S), AND EITHER ONE OF THE  @D@@@@. AND'S FAILZN
)@@G@@ED, OR ALL OF THEM PASSED, RESPECTIVELY.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          ONZO
)@@G@@        NSSP@F@@@@CHK900    LA,U      A3,MI0-1            . GET LAST ADDZP
)@@G@@R OF LI0    @G@@@@          J         CHK906              . GO ON FOR LEZQ
)@@G@@AD ITEM TESTS     @F@@@@CHK905    LA,U      A3,0700000          . MARK AZR
)@@G@@S MAIN ITEM CHECK @F@@@@CHK906    LA        A1,AOX              . GET ANZS
)@@G@@D/OR/XOR BITS     @G@@@@          AND,U     A1,OR+XOR           . GET JUZT
)@@G@@ST OR/XOR BITS IN A2    @G@@@@          L         R1,TESTS            . ZU
)@@G@@GET NUMBER OF TESTS TO DO     @E@@@@          JGD       R1,$+1          ZV
)@@G@@    . ADJUST FOR JGD    @E@@@@          LX        X2,(1,0)            . ZW
)@@G@@INITIALIZE INDEX  @I@@@@CHK910    TLE,H2    A3,INS1,X2          . L.I. CZX
)@@G@@HECK AND TEST OF STUFF IN M.I.?     @H@@@@          J         CHK925    ZY
)@@G@@          . YES, ASSUME TEST PASSED FOR NOW     @I@@@@          EX      ZZ
)@@G@@  INS1,X2             . EXECUTE REMOTE LOAD OF DIRECTORY INFO     @E@@@@AA
)@@G@@          TNZ       INS2,X2             . IS THIS A DTE?    @F@@@@      AB
)@@G@@    J         CHK920              . YES, SKIP AND/STORE     @F@@@@      AC
)@@G@@    AND       A0,TMASK,X2         . PERFORM 'AND' WITH MASK @F@@@@      AD
)@@G@@    SA        A1,SPC              . STORE RESULT IN SPC     @H@@@@      AE
)@@G@@    EX        INS2,X2             . EXECUTE REMOTE LOAD OF SPEC VALUE   AF
)@@G@@@G@@@@CHK920    EX        INS3,X2             . EXECUTE REMOTE TEST INSTAG
)@@G@@R     @D@@@@          J         CHK930              . TEST FAILED @F@@@@AH
)@@G@@CHK925    LA,U      A0,1                . MARK TEST SUCCEEDED     @C@@@@AI

)@@G@@  A0                  . MARK TEST FAILED  @]@@@@CHK940    . @H@@@@      AK

)@@G@@@I@@@@          JZ        A0,0,X11            . ONLY AND'S - IF ANY FAILAM

)@@G@@NE PASSED   @F@@@@CHK942    LA        A1,POLINK,X2        . GET POLISH TAO
)@@G@@BL INDEX    @H@@@@          SA        A0,POLISH,A1        . STORE RESULTAP
)@@G@@ OF TEST IN POLISH TABLE@F@@@@CHK944    NOP       0,0,*X2             . AQ

)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     ___@@@.     @G@@@@. CHK905 IS ENTRY POINT FOR MAAV

)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@ @@@@*.   @MFD GENERATION SKELETON @[@@@@*.    @^@@@@*.   SCX
)@@G@@GS'S ACCEPTED:    @[@@@@*.    @G@@@@*.   FULL ASSEMBLY      @PDP ALL PROCY
)@@G@@CS,, ASSEMBLE ALL ASM ELEMENTS,     @G@@@@*.                      AND PECZ

)@@G@@CORRECTIONS.@[@@@@*.    @F@@@@*.   UPDATE OPTION      PERFORM A SYMBOLICDB
)@@G@@ UPDATE, MERGING IN     @C@@@@*.                      THE PCF CORRECTIONDC
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@*.    @F@@@@*.   LIST OPTION        GENERATE LISTINGS OF EACDD
)@@G@@H ELEMENT WHICH IS@A@@@@*.                      PROCESSED.  @[@@@@*.    DE
)@@G@@@E@@@@*.   DO <EL1>,<EL2<     PROCESS THE SPECIFIED ELEMENT(S).   @F@@@@DF
)@@G@@*.                      IF A PROC IS SELECTED IN THIS MANNER,     @F@@@@DG
)@@G@@*.                      AND IT HAS PCF CORRECTIONS, ALL ELEMENTS  @B@@@@DH
)@@G@@*.                      WILL BE PROCESSED.@[@@@@*.    @F@@@@*.  NEW <ELEDI
)@@G@@MENT>       SPECIFIES THAT THIS ELEMNT EXISTS ONLY    @B@@@@*.          DJ
)@@G@@            IN THE PCF/TCF.   @[@@@@*.    @[@@@@*.    @#@@@@*DEFINE  PRODK
)@@G@@C     @]@@@@*IF [LIST]>0@A@@@@#HDG               ***   [#1]   *** @[@@@@DL
)@@G@@*END  @A@@@@*IF COLUMN SEARCH FROM NEW FOR [#1] @#@@@@#PDP,[#2]I   [#1] DM
)@@G@@@[@@@@*ELSE @#@@@@*IF [UPDATE]>0    @^@@@@#PDP,[#2]  [#1],[#1]    @[@@@@DN
)@@G@@*ELSE @^@@@@#PDP,[#2]  [#1],U-[#1]  @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*END  @#@@@@*CORREDO
)@@G@@CT [#1]     @[@@@@*END  @^@@@@*IF [#1] HAS CORRECTIONS@]@@@@*SET PDPCHG DP
)@@G@@@[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*.    @]@@@@*DEFINE PASM@]@@@@*IF [LIST]>0DQ
)@@G@@@A@@@@#HDG               ***   [#1]   *** @[@@@@*END  @A@@@@*IF COLUMN SDR
)@@G@@EARCH FROM NEW FOR [#1] @^@@@@#ASM,[#2]I    [#1],[#1] @[@@@@*ELSE @#@@@@DS
)@@G@@*IF [UPDATE]>0    @ @@@@#ASM,[#2]  [#1],[#1],[#1]     @[@@@@*ELSE @^@@@@DT
)@@G@@#ASM,[#2]  [#1],[#1]    @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*END  @#@@@@*CORRECT [#1]     DU
)@@G@@@[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*.    @F@@@@*CREATE SGS: ASM CHECK,DIREC$,DV
)@@G@@DIRERR,DIRLNK,DSEG,ID,INIT1,INIT2,; @E@@@@                 MFD,PRINT,PRIDW
)@@G@@NT2,QF,SORTER,TOTALS,WOUT     @^@@@@*CREATE SGS: PDP PROCS  @ @@@@*CREATDX
)@@G@@E SGS: MAP MAP,MFD,B    @#@@@@*CLEAR PDPCHG     @[@@@@*.    @ @@@@*INCREDY
)@@G@@MENT A TO [PDP,1,1]     @D@@_@*IF [FULL]>0 OR ROW SEARCH FROM DO FOR [PDDZ
)@@G@@P,1,1,A]    @]@@@@*IF [LIST]>0@ @@@@*PROCESS PROC [PDP,1,1,A] AL  @[@@@@EA
)@@G@@*ELSE @ @@@@*PROCESS PROC [PDP,1,1,A] A   @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@EB
)@@G@@*LOOP @[@@@@*.    @ @@@@*INCREMENT A TO [ASM,1,1]     @G@@_@*IF [FULL]>0EC
)@@G@@ OR PDPCHG IS SET OR ROW SEARCH FROM DO FOR [ASM,1,1,A]     @]@@@@*IF [LED
)@@G@@IST]>0@ @@@@*PROCESS PASM [ASM,1,1,A] SK  @[@@@@*ELSE @ @@@@*PROCESS PASEE
)@@G@@M [ASM,1,1,A] N   @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*END  @[@@@@*LOOP @[@@@@*.    @^@@@@EF
)@@G@@*INCREMENT A TO [MAP,1] @]@@@@*IF [LIST]>0@B@@@@#HDG               ***  EG
)@@G@@ [MAP,1,A,1]   ***@[@@@@*END  @]@@@@*EDIT ON    @#@@@@#MAP,[MAP,1,A,3]& EH

)@@G@@N   [MAP,1,A,1],[MAP,1,A,2]&  @[@@@@*END  @#@@@@*IF [UPDATE]>0    @#@@@@EJ
)@@G@@,[MAP,1,A,1]&     @[@@@@*END  @]@@@@*EDIT OFF   @^@@@@*CORRECT [MAP,1,A,EK

)@@G@@@[@@@@*END  ___         CORRECTIONS.@[@@@@*.    @F@@@@*.   UPDATE OPTIONEM
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@. DIREC$ IS AN NYU-WRITTEN SET OF ROUTINES FOR RETRIEVEN
)@@G@@ING INFORMATION   @H@@@@. FROM THE MASTER FILE DIRECTORY.  THE ROUTINES EO
)@@G@@INVOLVED ARE: DIREND, DIRINT, @^@@@@. DIRSEC, AND DIRLNK.   @D@@@@. EACHEP
)@@G@@ HAS BEEN WRITTEN TO BE CALLABLE FROM FORTRAN-V.@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. DIREEQ
)@@G@@ND - FREES DGET$ FILE AND ZEROES DRUM ADDRESS.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.    CER
)@@G@@ALLING SEQUENCE:  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIREND  @[@@@@ES
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LMJ   X11,DIREND   @E@@@@.                +ET
)@@G@@     0             . FORTRAN COMPATIBILITY@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@EU
)@@G@@. DIRINT - ASSIGNS DGET$ FILE ($$--DGET--$$) AND DOES DGET$.  DIRINT ATTEV
)@@G@@EMPTS @H@@@@.          TO DO A DOUBLE-BUFFERED DGET$, AND IF THAT FAILS EW
)@@G@@DUE TO AN EXEC    @G@@@@.          LOWER THAN 27-20-225, IT TRIES AGAIN EX
)@@G@@WITH A NORMAL DGET$.    @G@@@@.          A TAG 'DIRSIZ' EXISTS IN BOTH EEY
)@@G@@LEMENTS OF THE DIREC$ PACKAGE,@H@@@@.          DIREC$ AND DIRLNK.  THIS EZ
)@@G@@VALUE IS USED AS THE INITIAL RESERVE FOR  @H@@@@.          THE DGET$ FILFA
)@@G@@E.  IF THIS IS NOT ENOUGH, DIREC$ WILL TRY AGAIN USING@I@@@@.          TFB
)@@G@@HE SIZE RETURNED BY MSCON$ WHEN THIS OCCURS.  IF DIRSIZ IS CHANGED,     FC
)@@G@@@C@@@@.          IT MUST BE CHANGED IN BOTH ELEMENTS. @[@@@@.     @^@@@@FD
)@@G@@.    CALLING SEQUENCE:  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRINT($FE
)@@G@@ERR,ECODE,MASK,FORK)    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LMJ   X11,DIRFF
)@@G@@INT   @E@@@@.                +     ERTN          . ERROR RETURN ADDR    FG
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                +     ECODE         . ADDR OF 2-WORD ERROR CODE BFH
)@@G@@UFFER @D@@@@.                +     MASK          . ADDR OF MASK   @E@@@@FI
)@@G@@.                +     FORK          . ADDR OF FORK$ WORD   @E@@@@.     FJ
)@@G@@           +     0             . FORTRAN COMPATIBILITY@[@@@@.     @F@@@@FK
)@@G@@.    DIRINT MASK VALUES: (BITS MAY BE SET IN ANY COMBINATION)     @[@@@@FL
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.      IF BIT 0 IS SET, DON'T INITIALIZE DIRLNK @F@@@@.     FM
)@@G@@ IF BIT 1 IS SET, TELL DIRSEC TO GET LEAD ITEMS (SECTOR 0)  @F@@@@.     FN
)@@G@@ IF BIT 2 IS SET, DIRSEC WILL GET MAIN ITEMS (SECTOR 0)     @F@@@@.     FO
)@@G@@ IF BIT 3 IS SET, DIRSEC WILL PUT LEAD ITEMS IN BUFFER ADDR @E@@@@.     FP
)@@G@@   GIVEN IN DIRSEC CALL, AND MAIN ITEMS IN BUFFER+28. @F@@@@.      IF BOFQ
)@@G@@TH BITS 1&2 ARE SET, DIRSEC WILL RETRIEVE LEAD ITEMS  @F@@@@.        AS FR
)@@G@@WELL AS MAIN ITEMS, AND WILL RETURN WITH A0=0 IF IT   @G@@@@.        FOUFS
)@@G@@ND A LEAD ITEM, AND A0=1 IF IT FOUND A MAIN ITEM.  IF IT    @G@@@@.     FT
)@@G@@   IS DESIRED TO MOVE ON TO THE NEXT LEAD ITEM WITHOUT RETURNING  @H@@@@FU
)@@G@@.        ALL THE MAIN ITEMS FOR THE CURRENT LEAD ITEM, DIREC$'S EXTERNALFV
)@@G@@IZED  @G@@@@.        CELL 'GOTONE' SHOULD BE CLEARED BEFORE THE NEXT DIRFW
)@@G@@SEC CALL.   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.    FORK$ WORD - WHEN DOING A DOUBLE-BUFFFX
)@@G@@ERED DGET$, NO OTHER ACTIVITES MAY  @H@@@@.    BE ACTIVE.  IF THE FORK$ FY
)@@G@@WORD IS NON-ZERO, DIRINT WILL DO AN ER FORK$ TO @H@@@@.    THE ADDRESS SFZ
)@@G@@PECIFIED, AFTER THE ACTUAL DGET$ IS DONE.  IF THE FORK$ WORD@C@@@@.    CGA
)@@G@@ONTAINS 0, THEN NO ER FORK$ WILL BE DONE. @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@GB
)@@G@@. DIRSEC - GETS THE NEXT DESIRED ITEM FROM THE DGET$ FILE   @[@@@@.     GC
)@@G@@@^@@@@.    CALLING SEQUENCE:  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIGD
)@@G@@RSEC($ERR,ECODE,BUFF)   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LMJ   X11,DIRGE
)@@G@@SEC   @E@@@@.                +     ERTN          . ERROR RETURN ADDR    GF
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                +     ECODE         . ADDR OF 2-WORD ERROR CODE BGG
)@@G@@UFFER @G@@@@.                +     BUFF          . WHERE TO PUT THE INFOGH
)@@G@@RMATION     @E@@@@.                +     0             . FORTRAN COMPATIGI
)@@G@@BILITY@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.        SEE NOTES UNDER DIRINT     @[@@@@.     GJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@. DIRLNK - LINK TO ANOTHER LEAD ITEM/MAIN ITEM SECTOR @[@@@@.     GK
)@@G@@@^@@@@.    CALLING SEQUENCE:  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIGL
)@@G@@RLNK($ERR,ECODE,ITEM,LINK)    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LMJ   XGM
)@@G@@11,DIRLNK   @E@@@@.                +     ERTN          . ERROR RETURN ADGN
)@@G@@DR    @G@@@@.                +     ECODE         . ADDR OF 2-WORD ERROR GO
)@@G@@CODE BUFFER @D@@@@.                +     ITEM          . WHERE TO PUT ITGP
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                +     LINK          . ADDR OF LINK   @E@@@@.     GQ
)@@G@@           +     0             . FORTRAN COMPATIBILITY@[@@@@.     @[@@@@GR
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. ERROR CODES:    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. 1 - MSCON$ DGET$ ERRORGS
)@@G@@ (WORD 1 IS CONTENTS OF A0)   @D@@@@. 2 - I/O ERROR (WORD 1 IS CONTENTS GT
)@@G@@OF IOPACKET+3)    @^@@@@. 3 - EOF ON DIRSEC CALL@F@@@@. 4 - CSF$ ERROR OGU
)@@G@@N @ASG,T OF SCRATCH FILE (STATUS IS IN WORD 1)  @E@@@@. 5 - CALL MADE ONGV
)@@G@@ DIRSEC OR DIRLNK WHEN NOT INITIALIZED    @H@@@@. 6 - NUMBER OF DIRECTORGW
)@@G@@Y TRACKS TOO BIG - OVERFLEW ADDTBL IN DIRLNK DURING   @G@@@@.     INITIAGX
)@@G@@LIZATION.  INCREASE 'DIRSIZ' (CURRENT VALUE IN WORD 1).     @D@@@@. 7 - GY
)@@G@@BAD ADDRESS PASSED TO DIRLNK (ADDR IN WORD 1)   @D@@@@. 8 - ERROR RETURNGZ
)@@G@@ FROM ER MCT$ (STATUS IN WORD 1)    @B@@@@. 9 - BAD DIRINT MASK (MASK INHA
)@@G@@ WORD 1)    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@/$(1) @#@@@@          AXR$    @^@@@@DEBUG HB
)@@G@@    EQU       0   @G@@@@DIRSIZ*   EQU       0                   . DIRSIZHC
)@@G@@ IS THE INITIAL SIZE OF @E@@@@                                        . HD
)@@G@@THE DGET$ FILE.   @G@@@@                                        . IF THIHE
)@@G@@S IS NOT ENOUGH, DIREC$ @H@@@@                                        . HF
)@@G@@WILL FREE THE FILE AND REASSIGN     @G@@@@                              HG
)@@G@@          . IT WITH THE PROPER RESERVE.   @G@@@@                        HH
)@@G@@                . IF CHANGED, DIRLNK MUST BE    @E@@@@                  HI
)@@G@@                      . REASSEMBLED, ALSO.@B@@@@                        HJ
)@@G@@                . @I@@@@                                        . IF YOUHK
)@@G@@R DIRECTORY SIZE REMAINS FAIRLY     @H@@@@                              HL
)@@G@@          . STABLE (SAY, AROUND 150 TRACKS)     @G@@@@                  HM
)@@G@@                      . THEN YOU SHOULD SET DIRSIZ TO @H@@@@            HN
)@@G@@                            . THAT VALUE, PLUS SOME EXPANSION     @H@@@@HO
)@@G@@                                        . FACTOR.  IF, ON THE OTHER HANDHP
)@@G@@,     @G@@@@                                        . YOUR DIRECTORY SIZHQ
)@@G@@E KEEPS     @H@@@@                                        . INCREASING, HR
)@@G@@SET DIRSIZ TO ZERO.     @B@@@@                                        . HS
)@@G@@@D@@@@DIREND*   L         A0,FREE             . CHANGE CSFIM@D@@@@      HT
)@@G@@    LA        A1,CSFIM            . TO 'FREE'   @F@@@@          S       HU
)@@G@@  A0,CSFIM            . AFTER SAVING 'ASG,T'    @A@@@@          LA      HV
)@@G@@  A0,(4,CSFIM)    @^@@@@          ER        CSF$@E@@@@          SA      HW

)@@G@@C               . ZERO DRUM ADDRESS @C@@@@          J         1,X11     HY
)@@G@@          . RETURN@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DIRINT* .   @D@@@@      HZ
)@@G@@    S         X11,SAVX11          . SAVE X11    @E@@@@          L       IA

)@@G@@                . WANT LEAD ITEMS   @E@@@@          TEP,U     A0,4      IC

)@@G@@@E@@@@                                        . DYNAMIC EXPANSION @D@@@@IS

)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA        A2,SLASH            . '/     '    @F@@@@CN    IU
)@@G@@    SZ        A0                  . CONVERT TO FD DECIMAL   @ @@@@      IV
)@@G@@    DI,U      A0,10     @F@@@@          AA,U      A1,060              . IW

)@@G@@Z       A0,CN     @E@@@@          SA        A2,INTRES           . STORE IZ
)@@G@@IN ASG IMAGE@D@@@@          L,U       A0,CSFIM            . ASG FILE    JA

)@@G@@        MSCON$              . TRY DBDGET$ FIRST @E@@@@          JP      JD
)@@G@@  A0,DGETOK           . DID THAT GO OKAY? @F@@@@          L         A1,AJE

)@@G@@          S         A2,IOPAK+5          . NO,STRK   YES, READ TRACK     KP
)@@G@@@D@@@@          L         A0,(1792,TRKBUF)    . INTO TRKBUF @ @@@@      KQ
)@@G@@    S         A0,IOPAK+4@ @@@@          L,U       A0,IOPAK  @C@@@@      KR
)@@G@@    ER        IOW$                . DO IT @C@@@@          TZ,S1     IOPAKS
)@@G@@K+3             . IO OK?@F@@@@          SLJ       IOR                 . KT
)@@G@@NOPE, RETURN IO STATUS  @E@@@@NEWDX     L         A1,DX               . KU
)@@G@@GET TRACK INDEX   @G@@@@          A,U       A1,3                . INCREMKV
