)@@G@@       FUNCTIONEDITING  @G@@@@      THE FUNCTION EDITING CAPABILITIES OFHP
)@@G@@ APL\1100 DIFFER SLIGHTLY FROM@G@@@@ THOSE AVAILABLE ON  OTHER SYSTEMS, HQ
)@@G@@ ALTHOUGH THE COMMANDS  ARE TYPED IN@C@@@@ THE SAME FASHION.  THE COMMANHR
)@@G@@DS AVAILABLE ARE: @B@@@@        [N]    PREPARE TO ACCEPT LINE 'N' @E@@@@HS
)@@G@@        [N"]   PRINT LINE N, AND THEN PREPARE TO ACCEPT IT  @G@@@@      HT
)@@G@@  [N"M]  DISPLAY M LINES OF THE FUNCTION, STARTING WITH LINE N    @B@@@@HU
)@@G@@        ["]    DISPLAY THE ENTIRE FUNCTION@E@@@@        ["N]   ENTER CHAHV
)@@G@@NGE MODE FOR LINE N (SEE BELOW)     @G@@@@      THE MAJOR DIFFERENCE IN HW
)@@G@@APL\1100 FROM OTHER APL IMPLEMENTATIONS IS@G@@@@ IN THE METHOD  OF MAKINHX
)@@G@@G  CHANGES IN A  PARTICULAR LINE  OF A FUNCTION.@G@@@@ WHEN YOU TYPE THEHY
)@@G@@  FUNCTION MODE COMMAND ["N],  THE SYSTEM WILL DISPLAY@G@@@@ LINE N,  ANHZ
)@@G@@D THEN  MOVE  TO THE  LEFT MARGIN  AND  AWAIT A  LINE CHANGE@C@@@@ COMMAIA
)@@G@@ND.  LINE CHANGE COMMANDS ARE OF THE FORM:@B@@@@       /STRING1/STRING2/IB
)@@G@@              OR  @B@@@@       /STRING1/STRING2               OR  @ @@@@IC
)@@G@@       /STRING1/STRING2/ X    @G@@@@ THE FIRST NON-BLANK  CHARACTER (IN ID
)@@G@@THE  EXAMPLE ABOVE, A  / ) IS INTER-@G@@@@ PRETED AS A DELIMITER; IT  SEIE
)@@G@@PERATES STRING1 FROM STRING2.  THE PROGRAM@G@@@@ WILL EXAMINE  THE LINE IF
)@@G@@ BEING  EDITED FOR  THE  FIRST OCCURENCE  OF THE@G@@@@ CHARACTERS WHICH IG
)@@G@@MATCH  STRING1.  IF  THE FIRST  OF THE  ABOVE FORMS IS@G@@@@ USED, STRINIH
)@@G@@G1 WILL BE REPLACED BY THE CHARACTERS WHICH COMPRISE STRING2@G@@@@ (WHICII
)@@G@@H MAY BE NULL, THEREBY DELETING STRING1).  IN THE SECOND FORM, THE@G@@@@IJ
)@@G@@ FIRST OCCURENCE  OF  STRING1  WILL  BE  REPLACED  BY  STRING2,  AND THEIK
)@@G@@@G@@@@ REMAINDER OF  THE  IMAGE  WILL  BE  BLANKED.   ANY  NON-BLANK CHAIL
)@@G@@RACTER@G@@@@ APPEARING AFTER THE 3RD  DELIMITER (I.E. THE 'X'  IN THE THIM
)@@G@@IRD EXAMPLE)@G@@@@ WILL CAUSE ALL (RATHER THAN ONLY THE FIRST) OCCURENCEIN
)@@G@@S OF STRING1 TO BE@^@@@@ CHANGED TO STRING2.    @G@@@@       ONCE THE LIIO
)@@G@@NE  HAS BEEN  CHANGED, THE  NEWLY EDITED  LINE WILL BE@G@@@@ RE-DISPLAYEIP
)@@G@@D, AND  THE  SYSTEM  WILL WAIT  FOR  ANOTHER  EDITING CHANGE@G@@@@ COMMAIQ
)@@G@@ND.  WHEN ALL EDITING OF THE LINE HAS BEEN COMPLETED, A BLANK LINE@G@@@@IR
)@@G@@ (CARRIAGE RETURN) WILL  CAUSE THE  EDITED LINE TO  BE MADE  PART OF THEIS
)@@G@@@G@@@@ FUNCTION, AND  THE SYSTEM  WILL RETURN  TO THE  NORMAL FUNCTION EIT
)@@G@@DITING@[@@@@ MODE.@G@@@@      AT 1100 SERIES INSTALLATIONS WHICH HAVE INIU
)@@G@@STALLED THE  UNIVERSITY @G@@@@ OF MARYLAND  VERSION OF THE TEXT EDITING IV
)@@G@@  PROCESSOR @ED, AN ALTERNATE @G@@@@ MEANS OF EDITING  THE TEXT OF APL  IW
)@@G@@FUNCTIONS IS  AVAILABLE THROUGH THE @B@@@@ USE OF THE )EDIT COMMAND; THEIX
)@@G@@ COMMAND:   @A@@@@                    )EDIT   FUNCNAME@G@@@@ WILL INVOKEIY
)@@G@@ THE @ED PROCESSOR FOR EDITING   OF THE NAMED FUNCTION. @ED @G@@@@ IS A IZ
)@@G@@GENERAL PURPOSE   PROGRAM EDITOR   WITH  MANY FEATURES BEYOND THE @G@@@@JA
)@@G@@ SCOPE  OF   THIS  DOCUMENT; THE UOM  @ED   MANUAL SHOULD BE   USED FOR JB
)@@G@@@G@@@@ REFERENCE.   EXIT FROM THE EDITOR  (BACK TO   THE APL\1100 SYSTEMJC
)@@G@@)  IS @G@@@@ EFFECTED BY THE EDITOR COMMANDS  ABORT OR  EXIT . ABORT IS JD
)@@G@@USED IF THE @G@@@@ RESULTS OF  THE  EDITING  ARE  TO  BE DISCARDED. IF EJE
)@@G@@XIT IS  USED, THE @G@@@@ EDITED FUNCTION WILL BE ASSIMILATED BACK INTO TJF
)@@G@@HE ACTIVE WORKSPACE.    @G@@@@      THE )EDIT COMMAND MAY NOT BE USED IFJG
)@@G@@  ANY FUNCTIONS ARE SUSPENDED @G@@@@ IN THE STATE  INDICATOR; IN THIS CAJH
)@@G@@SE, THE INTERNAL EDITING FACILITIES @D@@@@ OF APL\1100 ITSELF (DESCRIBEDJI
)@@G@@ ABOVE) MUST BE USED.   @@@@@@@^@@@@       LIBRARYNUMBERS   @G@@@@      JJ
)@@G@@EACH USER OF THE APL\1100 SYSTEM IS GIVEN HIS OWN PRIVATE LIBRARY @G@@@@JK
)@@G@@ IN WHICH HE MAY ')SAVE'  WORKSPACES WITHOUT  REGARD TO WHETHER SOMEONE JL
)@@G@@@G@@@@ ELSE HAS )SAVE'D A WORKSPACE WITH THE  SAME NAME. EACH SUCH LIBRAJM
)@@G@@RY IS @G@@@@ UNIQUELY  IDENTIFIED BY A SO-CALLED 'LIBRARY NUMBER'. THE LJN
)@@G@@IBRARY NUM- @G@@@@ BER USED  IS CALCULATED FROM   THE  PARAMETERS OF THEJO
)@@G@@ EXEC-8 RUN, I.E. @G@@@@ RUNID AND/OR QUALIFIER  AND/OR ACCOUNT NUMBER. JP
)@@G@@USUALLY ONLY  QUALIFIER @G@@@@ AND ACCOUNT NUMBER ARE USED, BUT  THIS MAJQ
)@@G@@Y BE CHANGED AT LOCAL OPTION. @G@@@@ UNDER NORMAL CIRCUMSTANCES, ONE DOEJR
)@@G@@S NOT NEED TO KNOW WHAT HIS LIBRARY @G@@@@ NUMBER   IS; THE APL\1100   SJS
)@@G@@YSTEM WILL AUTOMATICALLY  GENERATE  IT AS @G@@@@ NEEDED. THE LIBRARY  NUJT
